If there is no query string parameter passed in to the url, the system should be able to extract the SSO Profile by interrogating the assertion provided during the SSO login process.
If the assertion contains a valid SSO Profile, that profile should be selected for user authentication.
To find the SSO Profile through the URI the customer can append the EntityId to the ACS URI
If the sso profile is not specified in the URI, the system logs this occurrence for auditing purposes.
If the sso profile is not specified in the URI then the system attempt to authenticate the user using the default SSO Profile (or First, when there is no IsDefault=true SSOProfile)
For user authentication the assertion should match the priority:   1. URL , 2. Is Default, 3. First() / fallthrough

When we have more than one profile but only one profile as isDefault as true and we change the value of that profile to false, a log message indicating that the IsDefault has being changed from true to false is present on Sumo Logic.

When we have more than one profile and isDefault value is set to false for all and one profile change the isDefault value to true then a summary log is created (SUMO) with just the old value and new value for isDefault field.

When we have one profile marked as isDefault value true and we change the isDefault value of another profile from false to true then a summary log is created (SUMO) with the old isDefault value and the new value for isDefault field

When we have one profile marked as isDefault value true and we change the isDefault value of another profile from false to true then a summary log is created (SUMO) with the old isDefault value and the new value for isDefault field
